            <biogHist>
                <p>Mary MacRae was born to parents Donald MacRae, a fisherman, and Chirsty MacRae
                    n√©e MacKenzie. At some stage prior to 1861 she moved to the Isle of Harris where
                    she worked as a servant, housekeeper and dairymaid. In the 1871 census, she is
                    recorded as being in Northton, Harris and as an aunt, possibly of one of the two
                    servants - Duncan MacRitchie and Mary MacDonald - who are recorded at the same
                    house. </p>
                <p>It appears she never married and died of old age, with a neighbour Anne MacRae as
                    witness; her recorded age at the time of death is given as 100, although this is
                    somewhat dubious.</p>
